LAGOS – Connect Nigeria, one of Nigeria’s leading business portals, has announced that April’s edition of its Business Mixer will take place this Friday in Lagos.Uzor Anekwe, Business Development Manager at Connect Nigeria, in a release said that top-level business owners, executives and others will be at the event to share ideas, adding that the event presents attendees with a golden opportunity to learn insights that will help them grow their businesses.According to him, “Connect Nigeria Business Mixer brings together leading entrepreneurs, corporate executives, and key decision-makers in the industry, in an environment that is primed for networking. Here you will meet with other forward-thinking business people, engage industry stakeholders, gain new vital business contacts, and set your enterprise up for growth.”The Business Development Manager at Connect Nigeria disclosed that this month’s edition of the Connect Nigeria Business Mixer will feature seasoned guests like Tolulope Medebem, Chief Operating Officer and Lead Consultant at Aster Integrated Marketing Limited and Blessing Abeng, Co-founder at Ingressive for Good. Others are Omoyeni Olulana, Head of Growth at Flex Finance and Olajumoke Oduwole, Co-founder and Chief Executive Officer at Alajo.Anekwe asserted that the guests would be sharing quality insights into building businesses that can thrive in Nigeria’s unique environment, and laying out actionable tips that can help your enterprise grow.